    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for a Medium model risk, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence COU. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) reflects the use of a single standardized ASTM F1717 test configuration; this limitation is accepted because all three primary QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) and the validation scenario is identical to the COU with no extrapolation required. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as credible for predicting compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
